                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d720">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/8–2344: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-23T09:00:00+07:00"
                            >August 23, 1944—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1449. According to local chief representative of China Defense Supplies in
                    liquidation, that organization is being terminated (our 1276, July 22) and China
                    lend-lease matters at this end are to be handled by Transport Commission or
                    Military Affairs Commission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
